Hello Parent_E—lovely to meet you, and thank you for considering Nursery_A. I’m happy to share how we run the day and how we support a calm, confident settling-in.

Daily routine (typical):
- Warm welcome & free play/choice time on arrival
- Morning circle (songs, stories, simple routines that build security)
- Small-group activities (language, early maths through play, creative, sensory)
- Outdoor time every day (gross motor, nature play)
- Lunch and rest/quiet time (tailored to age/need)
- Afternoon play, focused activities, and a calm pick-up handover

Transition/settling-in support:
- A gradual start plan: short visits with you present, then brief separations, building up at your child’s pace
- A consistent key-person approach so your child has a familiar adult for comfort and communication
- Predictable routines and visual cues to help children feel safe and know what comes next
- Close communication: we share how the day went (especially eating, sleep, mood, friendships) and agree on strategies together
- Comfort items are welcome (e.g., a small toy/blanket), and we use gentle, reassuring separation routines

If you share your child’s age and any particular needs (sleep, allergies, language, separation anxiety), I can explain how we’d tailor the settling-in plan. We’d be very pleased to receive an application from you when you’re ready.
